</p>

<p>
    Please bear in mind we have tested the offline application successfully on Google Chrome - some other browsers may not be supporting
    the new technologies we are leveraging yet.
</p>

<p>
    To use the offline application you just need to append <em>/mobile</em> to the address of your account.
</p>

<p>
    Your account URL: <br>
    <em>http://www.plancake,com/account.php</em>
</p>

<p>
    Offline application URL:<br />
    <em>http://www.plancake,com/account.php<b>/mobile</b></em>    
</p>

<p>
    The first time you reach the offline application (and after every time you clear your browser cache), your data
    will be synchronized and saved on your computer. From that moment on, your can use the mobile application even when offline. <br />
    <b>If you''re using a public or shared computer, don''t allow offline use.</b>    
</p>  

<p>
Every time you make a change, the modification will <b>NOT</b> be transfered to the Plancake servers automatically. Tasks changed locally will show a yellow border. 
</p>
    
<p>
Once you are ready to synchronise the data between your computer and the Plancake servers (and the other way around, too), click the ''Sync'' button at the bottom of the screen (you need an Internet connection only to do that).
</p>

